17:38.080 --> 17:40.040
♪ Early this morning ♪

17:42.920 --> 17:45.830
♪ When you knocked
upon my door ♪

17:49.460 --> 17:53.210
♪ And I say, "Hello, Satan ♪

17:53.210 --> 17:56.620
♪ I believe it's time to go" ♪

17:58.540 --> 18:01.670
Can't believe they let you
bring a blade around me.

18:01.670 --> 18:03.380
Just hold still.

18:06.920 --> 18:08.080
♪ Me and the devil ♪

18:11.620 --> 18:14.920
♪ Walkin' side by side ♪

18:14.920 --> 18:18.000
♪♪

18:18.000 --> 18:20.250
Tell me you slept better
than I did last night.

18:20.250 --> 18:22.620
Sleep's overrated.

18:22.620 --> 18:27.120
♪ Until I get satisfied ♪

18:27.120 --> 18:29.670
♪♪

18:29.670 --> 18:35.000
♪ Me and the devil ♪

18:35.000 --> 18:37.580
♪ Walkin' side by side ♪

18:37.580 --> 18:41.380
Michaela!
Over here!

18:41.380 --> 18:42.670
You made it.

18:42.670 --> 18:44.750
Yeah.
Did you get my text?

18:44.750 --> 18:46.960
Uh, my phone died.
How come you didn't come
to the hotel last night?

18:46.960 --> 18:49.580
I stayed up all night
with Annalise helping
her prep. It was crazy.

18:49.580 --> 18:51.620
Everyone,
this is Marcus --

18:51.620 --> 18:53.120
Walker. Yeah.

18:53.120 --> 18:55.330
Former press secretaries
need no introduction.

18:55.330 --> 18:57.210
Asher Millstone,
part-time law student,

18:57.210 --> 18:59.380
full-time
Michaela's boo.

18:59.380 --> 19:01.830
I hear you guys
need tickets.

19:01.830 --> 19:03.330
Let me check
with the guard.

19:03.330 --> 19:05.210
I'll come with,
in case you need backup.

19:07.080 --> 19:10.170
Michaela, please
tell me you didn't.

19:10.170 --> 19:12.080
-She totally did.
-I didn't.

19:12.080 --> 19:13.120
-Bang the press secretary.

19:13.120 --> 19:14.500
What?!

19:14.500 --> 19:16.920
Former press secretary.
And I didn't.

19:18.460 --> 19:20.330
Okay, I did, but it was
a one-time mistake.

19:20.330 --> 19:22.880
It meant nothing. Please don't
tell Asher. It'll destroy him.

19:22.880 --> 19:25.120
Destroy him like you destroyed
me when you stole this case?

19:25.120 --> 19:28.580
Hey, guys.
Main gallery.

19:28.580 --> 19:30.460
Marcus Walker
is the man!

19:30.460 --> 19:32.670
Boo-yah!

19:33.880 --> 19:36.540
-Pizza guy.

19:36.540 --> 19:38.670
The pizza delivery guy
is with Justice Strickland.

19:43.000 --> 19:45.000
Strickland's
working with Ingrid.

19:45.000 --> 19:46.670
Oh, my God.

19:46.670 --> 19:49.670
Let's have each of you sign
the Supreme Court guest book.

19:49.670 --> 19:52.830
Your signatures will join
the likes of Thurgood Marshall,

19:52.830 --> 19:55.620
F. Lee Bailey,
and Ruth Bader Ginsburg.

19:55.620 --> 19:57.880
Ms. Egan.

19:57.880 --> 20:00.040
Let Ms. Keating
go first.

20:00.040 --> 20:02.120
She's never
done this before.

20:04.710 --> 20:07.500
Clerk: Right here.

20:07.500 --> 20:12.670
♪♪

20:12.670 --> 20:17.620
♪♪

20:17.620 --> 20:19.920
She has no idea
what she's in for.

20:24.290 --> 20:25.960
It's Marcus.
I'll be right back.

20:25.960 --> 20:28.500
-No. Do your thing.

20:30.790 --> 20:32.170
You didn't tell me
you saw a pizza guy.

20:32.170 --> 20:33.580
What do you think
was in the box?

20:33.580 --> 20:34.830
Strickland's
prep questions.

20:34.830 --> 20:36.170
He's a hard-line
conservative.

20:36.170 --> 20:37.620
He wants to help Ingrid
any way he can.

20:37.620 --> 20:38.710
So Annalise is screwed.

20:50.540 --> 20:55.080
♪♪

20:55.080 --> 20:57.540
-Annalise.

20:57.540 --> 20:59.380
It's Jacqueline.

20:59.380 --> 21:04.210
I guess I should have
blocked my number days ago.

21:04.210 --> 21:07.620
Um, I've been out of town.

21:07.620 --> 21:08.710
You're in D.C.
I know.

21:08.710 --> 21:10.080
Which is why this
isn't a good time.

21:10.080 --> 21:13.080
Isaac overdosed,
Annalise.

21:13.080 --> 21:16.420
The police found him
in his car three days ago.

21:18.000 --> 21:19.460
Is he dead?

21:22.380 --> 21:25.580
No. But his kidneys
are failing.

21:25.580 --> 21:29.120
Do you get why I told you
to stay away now?

21:29.120 --> 21:30.830
This wasn't my fault.

21:30.830 --> 21:32.040
Telling me about Stella

21:32.040 --> 21:33.830
is what sent him to
this place, Annalise.

21:33.830 --> 21:35.380
You needed to know.

21:35.380 --> 21:37.620
I already knew.
But now look what you did.

21:39.170 --> 21:42.710
You ruined him, just like you
ruin everyone in your life.

21:44.920 --> 21:50.920
♪♪

21:54.170 --> 21:55.790
Isaac: I haven't felt
this bad since Stella died.

21:55.790 --> 21:57.120
Annalise: I'm with Isaac
and he's relapsed

21:57.120 --> 21:58.620
That's because of you.

21:58.620 --> 22:00.330
-His kidneys are failing.
-Ask him about Stella.

22:00.330 --> 22:01.790
Isaac: You really think
I'd be in this position
if it weren't for you?

22:01.790 --> 22:02.830
Jacqueline: Look what you did.
You ruined him...

22:02.830 --> 22:04.330
Annalise:
This wasn't my fault.

22:04.330 --> 22:05.710
Jacqueline: ...just like you
ruin everyone in your life.

22:05.710 --> 22:09.330
Isaac: And here I am. I'm just
sucked into your life!

22:19.460 --> 22:21.670
Your boss had you personally
deliver ex facto communications

22:21.670 --> 22:23.830
to Ingrid Egan the night
before oral arguments.

22:23.830 --> 22:26.290
You have no proof of that.
I have a photo of you
in a pizza uniform.

22:26.290 --> 22:27.790
You're bluffing.

22:27.790 --> 22:30.040
I'm Olivia Pope, Kevin.
I don't bluff.

22:30.040 --> 22:31.790
Get me in to see
Justice Strickland.

22:34.420 --> 22:36.000
Get back here, Kevin!

22:37.670 --> 22:39.580
What is it?

22:43.290 --> 22:45.330
This is because
of Strickland.

22:45.330 --> 22:47.920
I didn't get a chance
to tell her. I just walked
in, and she was like this.

22:47.920 --> 22:52.420
♪♪

22:52.420 --> 22:55.120
You okay?

22:56.540 --> 22:57.880
I can't do this.

22:57.880 --> 22:59.380
Of course you can.

22:59.380 --> 23:01.120
You have to.

23:01.120 --> 23:04.170
Annalise, no one else
can do this but you.

23:04.170 --> 23:05.710
No. I can't. All right?
It's you.

23:05.710 --> 23:07.920
You have to do this.
Please.

23:12.580 --> 23:14.290
No.

23:14.290 --> 23:16.710
No one knows the case
as good as you.

23:18.250 --> 23:19.920
I don't have standing
with the Court, Annalise.

23:19.920 --> 23:21.290
That's only you.

23:21.290 --> 23:22.670
-Mnh.
-So you need to talk to me.

23:22.670 --> 23:25.460
What do you need to walk
into that courtroom?

23:25.460 --> 23:28.710
Because that needs
to happen now.

23:28.710 --> 23:31.170
So tell me what you need,
and I will get it for you.

23:34.790 --> 23:37.040
Vodka.

23:40.880 --> 23:42.830
Okay.

23:46.250 --> 23:48.750
Go to Marcus.
Tell him to find vodka.

23:48.750 --> 23:50.120
She's an alcoholic. She'll
get disbarred if she drinks --

23:50.120 --> 23:51.330
-I know.
-That's just in normal court.

23:51.330 --> 23:52.880
-This is the Supreme Court.
-Michaela.

23:52.880 --> 23:55.920
Marcus. Vodka. Go.

24:02.880 --> 24:08.880
♪♪

24:11.710 --> 24:17.710
♪♪

24:20.210 --> 24:22.580
I need you.

24:22.580 --> 24:26.330
♪♪

24:26.330 --> 24:28.290
Something's wrong.

24:30.750 --> 24:34.580
Olivia, what if I fail?

24:34.580 --> 24:36.290
Then you fail.

24:36.290 --> 24:38.670
No, I can't. I can't.
I can't let these people down.

24:38.670 --> 24:40.000
Stop thinking
about those people.

24:40.000 --> 24:41.380
You said it yourself.

24:41.380 --> 24:43.000
You're not doing this
for them --

24:43.000 --> 24:47.540
for Nate, his father,
your mother, me.

24:47.540 --> 24:48.830
You're doing this
for you.

24:50.460 --> 24:53.920
You're doing this
for you.

24:53.920 --> 24:58.290
And for that little girl who
clawed her way out of Memphis

24:58.290 --> 25:01.330
after always being told
she wasn't good enough.

25:03.880 --> 25:06.040
Three minutes.
The countdown isn't making
anyone feel better, Oli.

25:08.670 --> 25:11.080
Oh, God.

25:12.670 --> 25:16.540
I can't believe I'm a grown-ass
woman asking for help.

25:16.540 --> 25:18.500
Well, you're a terrified
grown-ass woman.

25:21.330 --> 25:23.380
And I get that.

25:23.380 --> 25:25.000
What you're about to do
is terrifying.

25:25.000 --> 25:26.210
I'm terrified for you.

25:28.000 --> 25:30.830
But, Annalise,
this case chose you.

25:30.830 --> 25:35.120
So you need to pick yourself
off of this floor

25:35.120 --> 25:36.500
and walk into
that courtroom.

25:36.500 --> 25:39.250
Not for anybody else
but for you.

25:42.540 --> 25:46.250
Michaela: Here. Vodka.
We just don't have a cup.

25:46.250 --> 25:47.620
We only have
about two minutes.

25:47.620 --> 25:49.040
Get out.

25:49.040 --> 25:51.620
-But --
-You're not helping. Leave.

25:51.620 --> 25:56.290
♪♪

25:56.290 --> 25:59.120
Whatever it is you think is in
this bottle is already in you.

25:59.120 --> 26:02.580
I know that, but I don't have
time to convince you of that.

26:02.580 --> 26:04.960
So if you think you
need to drink, drink.

26:04.960 --> 26:10.960
♪♪

26:12.250 --> 26:18.250
♪♪

26:19.460 --> 26:22.540
Okay.

26:22.540 --> 26:23.750
Okay.

26:27.040 --> 26:28.960
-Okay.
-Okay.

26:30.460 --> 26:31.960
Okay.

26:31.960 --> 26:33.330
-Ready.
-Okay.

26:36.250 --> 26:37.620
Let's go.

26:37.620 --> 26:40.500
-1 minute, 45 seconds.
-Stop, Oliver.

26:40.500 --> 26:41.830
Oh, here she comes.

26:41.830 --> 26:44.830
Woman: Is that him?

26:47.790 --> 26:53.790
♪♪

26:55.250 --> 26:58.580
Okay, this may not be the
best time to tell you this,

26:58.580 --> 27:01.960
but Strickland's the
Justice who's been
feeding Ingrid information.

27:01.960 --> 27:04.460
You need to be ready
for him to gun for you.

27:04.460 --> 27:05.960
Anna Mae!

27:05.960 --> 27:08.380
Listen. You gotta eat
something, baby.

27:09.830 --> 27:13.880
You can't be keeling over
during a debate contest.

27:13.880 --> 27:16.380
-Please.
-Having a bit of an episode.

27:16.380 --> 27:18.380
Mama, we ate breakfast.
Remember?

27:18.380 --> 27:19.620
Just a sip. Just a little sip.
Just -- Just --

27:19.620 --> 27:21.040
Okay, okay.
Mrs. Harkness.

27:21.040 --> 27:24.080
How about I eat with you, and
Anna Mae can go to her debate?

27:24.080 --> 27:25.250
No.
Yes. Anna Mae --

27:25.250 --> 27:28.460
-Ophelia, let Anna Mae go.
-I said --

27:28.460 --> 27:29.420
-Ohh!

27:32.040 --> 27:34.790
-Annalise, go inside. Go.
-I'm sorry.

27:34.790 --> 27:37.210
It's okay. It's okay,
Mrs. Harkness.

27:37.210 --> 27:38.960
-I'm sorry.
-It's just...

27:38.960 --> 27:42.540
29, 28, 27, 26...

27:44.920 --> 27:46.880
There she is.

27:46.880 --> 27:52.880
♪♪

27:54.080 --> 27:56.540
Thought maybe
I'd scared you off.

27:56.540 --> 27:57.710
Not possible.

28:00.290 --> 28:02.830
Marshal of the Court:
The Honorable Chief Justice
and the Associate Justices

28:02.830 --> 28:05.380
of the Supreme Court
of the United States.

28:05.380 --> 28:08.120
Oyez! Oyez! Oyez!

28:08.120 --> 28:11.120
All persons having business
before the Honorable,

28:11.120 --> 28:13.330
the Supreme Court
of the United States,

28:13.330 --> 28:16.210
are admonished to draw near
and give their attention,

28:16.210 --> 28:18.170
for the Court is now sitting.

28:18.170 --> 28:21.420
God save the United States
and this Honorable Court.

28:21.420 --> 28:25.960
♪♪

28:31.380 --> 28:33.420
Mr. Chief Justice and
may it please the Court...

28:33.420 --> 28:35.580
Until my client,
Mr. Nathaniel Lahey,

28:35.580 --> 28:37.290
was 9 years old,

28:37.290 --> 28:40.580
it was illegal for him to sit
at a white-only counter.

28:40.580 --> 28:43.210
That changed when
Brown v. Board of Education

28:43.210 --> 28:45.000
ended segregation.

28:45.000 --> 28:49.170
Until he was 18, he had no right
to free legal counsel.

28:49.170 --> 28:51.710
Gideon v. Wainwright
ended that.

28:51.710 --> 28:54.580
At 20, Miranda v. Arizona

28:54.580 --> 28:57.540
stopped the police
from being able to arrest him

28:57.540 --> 29:00.670
without informing him
of his right to an attorney.

29:00.670 --> 29:03.250
With each of these
landmark decisions,

29:03.250 --> 29:06.790
this Court helped Mr. Lahey
get closer to the equality

29:06.790 --> 29:11.120
that our constitution promises
every citizen in this country.

29:13.080 --> 29:17.380
But he's still not there.
He's still not equal.

29:17.380 --> 29:20.500
Instead, he's the victim
of a broken system.

29:20.500 --> 29:23.620
!
-Yes, victim, Your Honor.

29:23.620 --> 29:27.000
Of repeated instances
of Sixth Amendment violations.

29:27.000 --> 29:30.170
Your client is a confessed
murderer, Ms. Keating.

29:30.170 --> 29:33.580
Justice Strickland, my client
was never informed of his right

29:33.580 --> 29:35.920
to appeal the sentence
after his first conviction.

29:35.920 --> 29:38.040
That's how ineffective
his counsel was.

29:38.040 --> 29:40.120
This is a version of the
story coming from him?

29:40.120 --> 29:42.500
Every one of
the 15 public defenders

29:42.500 --> 29:44.670
that he has had represent him

29:44.670 --> 29:46.250
told him to plead guilty.

29:46.250 --> 29:48.620
You're saying that
he was not guilty

29:48.620 --> 29:50.670
of any of these crimes?
Thank you.

29:50.670 --> 29:52.580
Without properly funded
counsel,

29:52.580 --> 29:55.380
he received sentences longer
than the average man.

29:55.380 --> 29:58.380
And these years in prison
included solitary confinement,

29:58.380 --> 30:00.380
which resulted
in mental-health issues

30:00.380 --> 30:02.290
that led to the tragic events
of this murder.

30:02.290 --> 30:05.620
But you just said that
your client was the victim.

30:05.620 --> 30:08.460
The victim of underfunded
public defense system.

30:08.460 --> 30:09.670
Don't interrupt me.

30:11.330 --> 30:14.460
Ophelia: I'm so sorry.
Really I am.

30:14.460 --> 30:17.620
I'm fine. Mrs. Harkness, you
need to go watch Anna Mae.

30:17.620 --> 30:20.710
Anna Mae doesn't need her mama
right now. She needs you.

30:20.710 --> 30:23.500
No, I think she'll be fine
all on her own.

30:23.500 --> 30:26.670
Stop yapping and go sit --
sit your butt down.

30:26.670 --> 30:30.540
The only victim in this case
is Gerald Reinhoff,

30:30.540 --> 30:33.080
the man that your client
beat to death in cold blood.

30:33.080 --> 30:35.250
We are not here
to try a murder,

30:35.250 --> 30:37.790
but to understand the events
that led up to this murder.

30:37.790 --> 30:40.120
But of all the plaintiffs
that you could've brought us,

30:40.120 --> 30:42.040
you're asking us
to feel for a killer?

30:42.040 --> 30:43.210
A man the system
made into a killer.

30:43.210 --> 30:45.250
I said don't interrupt.

30:45.250 --> 30:47.380
Justice Strickland:
Now, what is apparent to me

30:47.380 --> 30:49.420
and to several of
my fellow Justices...

30:49.420 --> 30:50.880
Let's not speak
for the rest of us.

30:50.880 --> 30:52.580
...is that this
is a money issue,

30:52.580 --> 30:55.460
one that the legislature
of Pennsylvania can decide.

30:55.460 --> 30:58.500
Except this case is not only
about money, Your Honor.

30:58.500 --> 31:00.920
It's about race.

31:02.830 --> 31:06.040
You're just like
Anna Mae.

31:06.040 --> 31:09.670
Always taking care of
everybody else but yourself.

31:12.000 --> 31:14.040
Oh, I see it on the TV.

31:16.000 --> 31:20.750
Sometimes, you're standing
next to the man president.

31:22.330 --> 31:24.290
Then the lady president.

31:26.000 --> 31:28.250
Fixin'.

31:28.250 --> 31:30.620
Fixin', fixin', fixin'.

31:32.920 --> 31:37.960
Sometimes that doesn't leave you
any time for yourself.

31:37.960 --> 31:41.380
I know this.

31:41.380 --> 31:43.330
Because I was you.

31:43.330 --> 31:47.040
I mean, not hanging
with no presidents

31:47.040 --> 31:48.250
or anything like that.

31:48.250 --> 31:51.620
Just...
people needed me.

31:54.500 --> 31:58.040
People needed me.

31:58.040 --> 32:00.000
That's for sure.

32:04.460 --> 32:06.960
Sometimes, I think
this whole country

32:06.960 --> 32:10.750
would just fall apart...

32:10.750 --> 32:15.170
if we weren't around to...

32:15.170 --> 32:18.120
clean up all the mess.

32:22.830 --> 32:24.420
Only, this time...

32:27.960 --> 32:29.580
...I made the mess.

32:31.540 --> 32:34.210
Hmm? Mnh.

32:34.210 --> 32:38.040
You were just
being a good mom.

32:38.040 --> 32:41.670
One in three black men
will go to prison

32:41.670 --> 32:43.460
versus one in 17
white men.

32:43.460 --> 32:45.710
Either you are arguing
that your plaintiffs

32:45.710 --> 32:48.500
are getting
ineffective counsel

32:48.500 --> 32:51.540
because of poor funding
or because of their race.

32:51.540 --> 32:53.330
-Both.

32:53.330 --> 32:55.330
Not all of your plaintiffs
are people of color.

32:55.330 --> 32:56.670
My sample of plaintiffs

32:56.670 --> 32:59.620
matches a racial breakdown
of incarceration.

32:59.620 --> 33:03.080
40% of my plaintiffs are black.
20% are Latino.

33:03.080 --> 33:04.830
If you want us to
consider race here,

33:04.830 --> 33:06.880
it would have to be
the determining factor.

33:06.880 --> 33:08.080
It's one of many factors.

33:08.080 --> 33:11.040
But is it the
determining factor?

33:11.040 --> 33:13.460
Either it is
or it isn't.

33:13.460 --> 33:19.460
♪♪

33:21.580 --> 33:23.540
Yes.

33:23.540 --> 33:25.380
Race is the
determining factor.

33:25.380 --> 33:27.620
Oh.

33:27.620 --> 33:29.500
You did not file
this class action

33:29.500 --> 33:31.830
on the grounds
of discrimination,

33:31.830 --> 33:34.710
so we cannot consider race
in our decision.

33:34.710 --> 33:36.290
I disagree.

33:36.290 --> 33:37.920
This bench must
consider the validity

33:37.920 --> 33:39.620
of Ms. Keating's equal
protection argument.

33:39.620 --> 33:42.080
Chief Justice Montgomery: The
impact of a ruling based on race

33:42.080 --> 33:43.750
would have adverse
procedural implications.

33:43.750 --> 33:46.080
That was the argument
in Brown v. Board.

33:46.080 --> 33:48.120
Segregation was designed
to discriminate.

33:48.120 --> 33:49.710
Can't say the same thing...

33:49.710 --> 33:51.330
Olivia: Don't lose a second
of your 30 minutes.

33:51.330 --> 33:52.500
Every word matters.

33:52.500 --> 33:55.250
...Court decided the effects
of racism were so...

33:55.250 --> 33:56.460
So let us listen
to Ms. Keating.

33:56.460 --> 33:58.040
Justice Strickland:
Let me say this again.

33:58.040 --> 34:01.540
Race is not a variable
in this case.

34:01.540 --> 34:03.540
Your Honor, I'd like to use

34:03.540 --> 34:05.790
the remainder of my time
to prepare my rebuttal.

34:05.790 --> 34:07.500
Chief Justice Montgomery: The
request for rebuttal is granted.

34:10.540 --> 34:13.620
Mr. Chief Justice
and may it please the Court,

34:13.620 --> 34:17.580
Ms. Keating has pulled
a bait-and-switch on this Court.

34:17.580 --> 34:20.580
The minute she made race
the determining factor,

34:20.580 --> 34:22.170
she took it out of the
purview of this trial...

34:22.170 --> 34:24.000
Go to the library and
look up this ruling.

34:24.000 --> 34:25.040
-Okay.
-Michaela.

34:25.040 --> 34:27.040
We lose without it.

34:27.040 --> 34:29.920
Ingrid: ...race but
on the expertise of
the individual attorney.

34:29.920 --> 34:33.250
In Washington v. Davis,
your predecessors decided

34:33.250 --> 34:36.580
that even if a law has
a discriminatory effect,

34:36.580 --> 34:37.750
it is unconstitutional...
You did your best.

34:37.750 --> 34:39.920
if that was not
its intended purpose.

34:39.920 --> 34:41.500
If that is the precedent that
Ms. Keating wants to challenge,

34:41.500 --> 34:43.330
then that case
needed to be built

34:43.330 --> 34:45.920
and argued in the
state appellate courts.

34:45.920 --> 34:47.330
Bryant v. Topeka.
Topeka means Kansas,

34:47.330 --> 34:49.500
which means it has to be
in the 10th circuit.

34:49.500 --> 34:52.330
So I'll start with
the indexes from '82.

34:52.330 --> 34:54.420
You start with '87, and we'll
meet somewhere in the middle.

34:55.580 --> 34:56.880
Why are you looking
at me like that?

34:56.880 --> 34:59.290
Your brain. It's hot.

34:59.290 --> 35:01.420
Focus.

35:01.420 --> 35:02.920
Justice Spivey:
Washington v. Davis was

35:02.920 --> 35:05.290
decided on a technical issue
of the lower courts

35:05.290 --> 35:07.500
for not applying
appropriate legal standards.

35:07.500 --> 35:10.540
Ingrid: While Ms. Keating's
statistics make it clear

35:10.540 --> 35:13.080
that our judicial system
should be reformed,

35:13.080 --> 35:14.710
that is not the duty
of this Court today.

35:18.540 --> 35:22.210
Ms. Keating, we'll now hear
your rebuttal arguments.

35:22.210 --> 35:28.210
♪♪

35:30.620 --> 35:36.620
♪♪

35:44.420 --> 35:46.750
"As an arbiter of the law,
with whole knowledge

35:46.750 --> 35:49.580
of historical jurisprudence
in this country,

35:49.580 --> 35:52.000
race must always be
considered a variable."

35:52.000 --> 35:53.330
You have precious time,
Ms. Keating.

35:53.330 --> 35:55.330
I suggest that
you don't waste it

35:55.330 --> 35:58.330
by making arguments
you've already made.

35:58.330 --> 36:00.960
These are not my words,
Justice Strickland.

36:00.960 --> 36:03.000
They're yours.

36:03.000 --> 36:08.120
You wrote them in your
1985 ruling in Bryant v. Topeka,

36:08.120 --> 36:09.540
an equal protection case

36:09.540 --> 36:12.330
dealing with a state-housing
lottery program.

36:12.330 --> 36:17.920
♪♪

36:17.920 --> 36:23.210
Racism is built
into the DNA of America.

36:23.210 --> 36:26.120
And as long as
we turn a blind eye

36:26.120 --> 36:29.210
to the pain of those suffering
under its oppression,

36:29.210 --> 36:32.380
we will never escape
those origins.

36:32.380 --> 36:36.000
The only safeguard
people of color have

36:36.000 --> 36:37.670
is the right to a defense,

36:37.670 --> 36:39.920
and we won't even
give them that.

36:39.920 --> 36:42.380
Which means that the promise
of civil rights

36:42.380 --> 36:45.420
has never been fulfilled.

36:45.420 --> 36:47.880
Due to the failure
of our justice system,

36:47.880 --> 36:50.290
our public defense system
in particular,

36:50.290 --> 36:53.750
Jim Crow is alive and kicking --

36:53.750 --> 36:56.500
laws that made it illegal
for blacks and whites

36:56.500 --> 36:58.670
to be buried
in the same cemetery,

36:58.670 --> 37:02.170
that categorized people
into quadroon and octaroons,

37:02.170 --> 37:03.580
that punished a black person

37:03.580 --> 37:06.790
for seeking medical attention
in a white hospital.

37:09.960 --> 37:13.120
Some may claim
that slavery has ended.

37:13.120 --> 37:15.710
But tell that to the inmates
who are kept in cages

37:15.710 --> 37:19.040
and told that they don't have
any rights at all.

37:19.040 --> 37:21.380
People like my client,
Nathaniel Lahey,

37:21.380 --> 37:23.250
and millions of people like him

37:23.250 --> 37:26.210
who are relegated to
a subclass of human existence

37:26.210 --> 37:27.960
in our prisons.

37:27.960 --> 37:32.000
There is no alternative
to justice in this case.

37:32.000 --> 37:34.460
There is no other option.

37:34.460 --> 37:37.380
To decide against my plaintiff

37:37.380 --> 37:40.790
is to choose lining the pockets
of prison owners

37:40.790 --> 37:45.290
over providing basic defense
for the people who live in them.

37:45.290 --> 37:47.670
And is that the America

37:47.670 --> 37:50.790
that this Court
really wants to live in?

37:50.790 --> 37:54.120
Where money is more important
than humanity?

37:54.120 --> 37:56.750
Where criminality is confused
with mental health?

37:56.750 --> 38:02.670
♪♪

38:02.670 --> 38:06.750
The Sixth Amendment
was ratified in 1791.

38:06.750 --> 38:10.170
It's been 226 years since then.

38:10.170 --> 38:14.460
Let's finally guarantee its
rights to all of our citizens.

38:14.460 --> 38:20.460
♪♪

38:29.420 --> 38:31.080
Reporter #1: The word is
Ms. Keating won over

38:31.080 --> 38:32.710
some of the
more moderate Justices.

38:32.710 --> 38:35.170
Trying to predict what the Court
will decide is a fool's errand.

38:35.170 --> 38:37.000
Reporter #2: Ms. Keating,
what is your response to critics

38:37.000 --> 38:39.380
who say you are attacking
public defenders?

38:39.380 --> 38:41.000
Tell them to see me
when they get

38:41.000 --> 38:42.960
more time and money
to argue their cases.

38:42.960 --> 38:44.790
Reporter #1: She did catch
Justice Strickland

38:44.790 --> 38:46.500
in direct contradiction
of his previous ruling.

38:46.500 --> 38:48.580
Justices are allowed to
evolve in their thinking.

38:48.580 --> 38:50.880
In fact, I think that's called
wisdom. Next question.

38:50.880 --> 38:52.290
Reporter #2:
Do you think you won in there?

38:52.290 --> 38:55.380
Oh, win or lose, I'd like to
give a shout-out to my team,

38:55.380 --> 38:59.000
and that includes my named
plaintiff, Nathaniel Lahey.

38:59.000 --> 39:00.710
I hope that this
is a first step

39:00.710 --> 39:02.620
in getting him the fair
and proper defense

39:02.620 --> 39:06.080
that he never received
during his 33 years in jail.

39:06.080 --> 39:08.920
Dad, I'd like you to
meet Annalise's parents.

39:08.920 --> 39:12.380
It's a pleasure
to meet you, Mr. Lahey.

39:13.710 --> 39:18.000
You're a...
very brave man, sir.

39:18.000 --> 39:20.250
Not half as brave
as your daughter.

39:20.250 --> 39:21.460
Well, thank you.

39:24.620 --> 39:26.920
Annalise: I had a great team
of smart people

39:26.920 --> 39:28.670
that helped me
get this case heard --

39:28.670 --> 39:30.790
several of my former
law students,

39:30.790 --> 39:32.580
Connor Walsh in particular,

39:32.580 --> 39:35.420
as well as members
of the Grant Institute

39:35.420 --> 39:37.920
that really pushed the Court
to hear this case.

39:37.920 --> 39:40.620
And that includes someone
that you all know --

39:40.620 --> 39:41.790
Olivia Pope.

39:43.960 --> 39:45.880
Did you know Ms. Pope
before working together

39:45.880 --> 39:47.420
-Do you see the two of you

39:47.420 --> 39:49.210
working together
in the future?

39:49.210 --> 39:50.290
Frank: Hey.

39:50.290 --> 39:51.830
Yeah, there no money
in Wes' account.

39:51.830 --> 39:54.250
What about a Swiss bank account
or something?

39:54.250 --> 39:56.670
Tell Laurel already,
Frank.

39:56.670 --> 40:02.710
♪♪

40:03.960 --> 40:05.750
Frank:
Come on, Barbie.

40:05.750 --> 40:08.580
Mommy said you took the money,
so where's your hiding spot?

40:08.580 --> 40:14.580
♪♪

40:17.290 --> 40:23.290
♪♪

40:26.080 --> 40:32.080
♪♪

40:35.080 --> 40:37.710
Frank, if this is some
sort of relationship talk,

40:37.710 --> 40:39.210
I'm too tired.

40:39.210 --> 40:42.500
Laurel. Your mom's
been lying to you.

40:47.420 --> 40:50.040
Sandrine: You're having
legal trouble.

40:50.040 --> 40:52.580
Wallace Mahoney
was killed.

40:52.580 --> 40:54.080
Wes: Not sure what that
has to do with me.

40:54.080 --> 40:56.790
But you've had other troubles
with the police, no?

40:56.790 --> 41:00.420
Okay, I'm telling
Laurel about this.

41:03.250 --> 41:05.880
Okay. I'll tell her.

41:08.790 --> 41:10.330
That was President Grant.

41:10.330 --> 41:12.670
He said the Justices might
be swinging in our favor.

41:12.670 --> 41:14.750
I'll believe it when
I see it in writing.

41:14.750 --> 41:17.670
Smart.

41:17.670 --> 41:19.460
Now, when you get home,

41:19.460 --> 41:21.710
I've set a meeting with
the Pennsylvania Bar Review.

41:21.710 --> 41:23.620
They're gonna do
a profile on you.
No.

41:23.620 --> 41:25.960
You say yes to every interview,
no to every book offer.

41:25.960 --> 41:28.500
You're done, okay?

41:28.500 --> 41:30.710
You don't have to
handle me anymore.

41:33.920 --> 41:35.580
We did good.

41:36.790 --> 41:38.830
Yeah.

41:40.330 --> 41:43.420
Take care
of yourself, Annalise.

41:55.500 --> 41:58.250
Bonnie. I was just
about to call you.

41:58.250 --> 42:01.710
Annalise,
I'm so sorry to do this,

42:01.710 --> 42:02.790
but I'm at the hospital.

42:04.960 --> 42:06.540
Is it Isaac?

42:06.540 --> 42:09.620
No.

42:09.620 --> 42:11.620
It's Simon.

42:11.620 --> 42:13.830
He's awake.

42:13.830 --> 42:19.830
♪♪

42:29.420 --> 42:35.420
♪♪

42:36.620 --> 42:42.620
